  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis ML surrogate credibility assessment (nominal validation only)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis (relative hemolysis index, RH) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. The surrogate replaces a high-fidelity CFD solver for rapid design-space exploration across component-dimension tolerances. Validation evidence is drawn exclusively from held-out samples of the same experimental campaign used for training; no distribution-shift, noise-injection, or adversarial perturbation studies are included. One out-of-distribution operating point (flow = 7 L/min, speed = 3200 RPM) was evaluated post-hoc and cited as evidence that the model 'generalizes well beyond the training envelope,' but no statistical characterization of generalization error under covariate shift is provided. All 13 ASME V&V 40 factors are assessed at MRL 2.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-ml-surrogate-rh-criterion",
