      "rationale": "The surrogate outputs RH directly, matching the regulatory QoI. Feature importance analysis confirms that impeller tip speed and gap clearance — the primary design variables of interest — are the dominant predictors (combined SHAP contribution > 70%). The QoI is clinically and regulatorily relevant for Class II CPB device assessment."
