      "acceptanceCriteria": "All five model input features are measurable, traceable to physical parameters in the COU, and have documented uncertainty budgets.",
      "rationale": "Input features (volumetric flow rate ±0.5%, rotational speed ±10 RPM, gap clearance ±0.01 mm, impeller outer diameter ±0.02 mm, blade exit angle ±0.5°) are all directly measurable with traceable calibration. Uncertainty propagation through the surrogate was performed via Monte Carlo sampling (N=10,000) over the nominal input uncertainty ranges, yielding a 95th-percentile RH prediction interval of ±0.048. Input uncertainty characterization covers nominal manufacturing tolerances only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
