    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in validation experiments are equivalent to those in the intended COU deployment context.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the same FDA generic centrifugal blood pump hardware, the same glycerol-water blood analogue at 40% hematocrit and 37°C, and the same flow-speed combinations as the COU. Dimensional analysis confirms dynamic similarity between validation and COU conditions (Reynolds number and flow coefficient match within 2%). Equivalency is established for the nominal COU envelope; equivalency under shifted input distributions (e.g., different hematocrit, temperature excursions, or geometric outliers) has not been assessed."
