    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The gradient-boosted ensemble surrogate achieves MAE = 0.031 and R² = 0.974 on the nominal test set, correctly ranking worst-case hemolysis conditions in 98.3% of cases. The single out-of-distribution evaluation at 7 L/min / 3200 RPM yielded a 4.4% relative error, which the assessment team interprets as evidence of adequate generalization. The surrogate is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the specified COU. Robustness to distribution shift, noise, and adversarial perturbation was not formally characterized; the assessment team considers this acceptable at MRL 2 given that model influence is Medium and experimental testing confirms final design decisions.",
